# (b) Workflow on the Capability frontend (P-20 — workflow-on-Backend)
#     Multi-step orchestration (trigger → poll → fetch, retry, or blocking-call sequencing)
#     belongs on the Backend, NEVER on the Capability frontend. The Capability frontend stays
#     a thin @need_capability_ready forward so different backends can pick different
#     completion strategies (polling, callbacks, blocking calls).
#     Documented in: PR #1009 (Micronic) Finding 2; Echo branch Finding 3 — same contributor.
#
# (c) Capability bypass via Device convenience methods (P-02 / P-06)
#     Convenience methods on this Device that map to a Capability operation MUST go through
#     self.<capability>.<method>, NEVER through self.driver.<method>.
#     - Genuinely device-level (e.g., serial-number query, firmware version): self.driver — OK
#     - Capability-shaped (e.g., "is plate present?"): self.<capability>.<method> — REQUIRED
#     If a Capability operation has no Capability-frontend method, the right shape is to add
#     one to the Capability + Backend ABC, not to expose it on the Device alone.
#     Documented in: Echo branch Finding 5.

